Migrate rnnr.c to rnnoise's current `rnnoise_model_from_file` API

Upstream Thetis' rnnr.c was written against an older rnnoise that
exported `rnnoise_model_from_filename(const char*)`. Current
rnnoise master dropped that wrapper in favour of the lower-level
`rnnoise_model_from_file(FILE*)`, which takes a caller-opened
stdio handle. The change was part of a broader symbol-rename
cleanup (`use rnn_ prefix for non-exported symbols`, commit
6cbfd53) — the underlying file format stays identical.

The fix is a 7-line conversion at the single call site in
`RNNRloadModel()`: fopen the file, call the new API, fclose.
Nothing else in rnnr.c touches the rnnoise surface so this is the
only mismatch.

We intentionally vendor rnnoise at its current upstream HEAD
rather than pinning v0.2 (Aug 2022) so that future phase-B
improvements to the NN model land automatically. Upstream WDSP
itself can't keep up because it's archived — hence this small
patch on our side.

--- a/rnnr.c
+++ b/rnnr.c
@@ -368,7 +368,13 @@ void RNNRloadModel(const char* file_path)
     // try to load
     if (file_path && file_path[0])
     {
-        _rnnr_model = rnnoise_model_from_filename(file_path);
+        FILE* fp = fopen(file_path, "rb");
+        if (fp)
+        {
+            _rnnr_model = rnnoise_model_from_file(fp);
+            fclose(fp);
+        }
+        // If fopen fails, _rnnr_model stays NULL (baked-in model).
     }

     // recreate any we had created previously and restart if needed
